NY positive things happening in Iraq along with the problems there. I think its a disservice to our cause for the government not to present the "plan" in a way that your average American can consume.<br /><br />What it means to be working tward Democratic, Capitalist, and Humanitarian goals. How that contrasts with what they had and how they really feel about the struggle the Iraqis are living through today. A poll recently taken of the Iraqi people shows a 70ish % of the population is for the removal of Sadam, 60someodd % say it things are harder than they were  before (rightly so) and the majority of those think in the long term this is the future they want. As an american I am VERY proud of that as opposed to how proud i'd be if I was french right about now.<br /><br /><br /><br /></span></font></td>
