e welfare of the US economically. Saudi Arabia would have been on the list of "Axis of Evil" states had it not been for the effect oil prices would wage on our economy. We are having to play a dangerous game of pick the badguy out of a bag that provides your next 50 years of oil. I'd also wage a guess that IF they did, every damn liberal who is claming "WHY NOT SAUDI ARABIA, DON'T YOU KNOW 19 OF THE HIJACKERS WERE FROM SAUDI ARABIA... F'N HYPOCRITS" would be singing to the toon of "WTF Why are my gas prices 11 dollars a gallon." and we'd have a nice fat economical meltdown settin off right about now.<br /><br />Lastly, I'm all for taking out dictators, I say hell yeah, but I also understand/assume we at the VERY least take a look at who the fluck is going to replace said dictator once we do it.. it does absolutely no good to start picking off dictatorA and have them replaced by dictatorB. It obviously costs alot of money to prop a new government up after we do it, we should pick and choose who we do it to and make it count when we do it.<br /><br />Thats my story and I'm stickin to it, unless of course Drex starts chewin into me.. then I'll start positioning myself as a Communist sympathizer <img src="images/batman_125.gif" border="0" alt="" title="" align="middle" /></span></font></td>
